        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 2:39AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 239 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Stratford, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stratford and Griggs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
